<Author>DenverProfessor1
<Content>Just OK First, the good news. The location is excellent. Within walking distance of many sites within the old city and a very short walk to the Liceu metro stop. Our room overlooked the square below and the view was great. The two different people operating the front desk while we stayed there were very helpful and spoke English. Next, the bad news. The walls are thin and we could hear the people in the next room adjacent to the head of our bed. Also, there was a waste water line also near the head of the bed. One could hear the water noisely rushing down as the toilets and showers above were used. The bathroom smelled like the waste lines were not vented correctly and the bath fan could not get rid of the smell. The room and the bath were small. The shower was tiny.The optional breakfast was good but expensive relative to what one could get in El Ravel, a short walk away. 
