<Author>on-a-coffee-break
<Content>Superb location This hotel is in a great location just off the Rambles within minutes walk of many sights and the Metro for visiting things further afield. It is just a short walk from Placa Catalunya too where you can catch the A1 airport bus for getting in an out of the city for a few Euros. Do be aware this is not a luxury hotel and you get what you pay for. The rooms are small and it can be quite noisy - especially as it is on a busy square with two cafes in the heart of the city and the walls of the rooms are thin. However I've been to Barcelona several times and have generally found most hotels to be pretty dire unless you pay big money - this being the best cheaper one I've found so far with the superb location being the best aspect. For other things to do, on weekends there are farmers and artists markets on the square. If you are fit and fancy a different way of seeing the city, hire bikes from the end of the Rambles (under the Columbus Statue). If you fancy posh tapas the Taller de Tapas restaurant on the same square is excellent. There are frequent spanish guitar concerts in the church on the square as well. For all other things the hotel reception staff are friendly and very helpful. Don't pay for breakfast, the cafes on the square are half the price. Overall an enjoyable stay. I will use this hotel again. 
