<Author>SpikeDaisy
<Content>Great Location This hotel is located on a relatively quiet square just off the Ramblas. It is an awesome location to be close to all the action without having to sleep right on it. Depending on the staff members present the service can range from wonderful to below average. Be aware that if you ask for restaurant recommendations, they may recommend a place they get a commission from. The rooms are basic and clean. Not anything to complain about for the location and value. A few drawbacks were no computer for internet access (they do have free wi-fi in the lobby), and some staff were not particularly helpful.Just a few tips to hopefully enjoy your time in Barcelona better: Bus Turistic is a handy and convenient way of seeing all the sites in the city. The sites in Barcelona are a little more spread out than some other cities (ie Madrid). You can hop on/hop off at the major sites. The tickets for a one day pass are 23 euros and 26 for two days. You get a coupon booklet that almost pays for half of your ticket price to most major sites. There is a great tapas bar located really close to the hotel called Taverna Basca Irati. Also make sure to try Cafe de l'Academia for a nice dinner. It is about a 10 minute walk from the hotel just off of Placa S. Jaume. It was our favorite restaurant during our whole trip in Spain. Make sure to have reservations, otherwise you may not have much luck getting a table. About 13 euros per plate. 
