<Content>Do NOT stay here If you don't mind staying in a hostel like atmosphere, but paying for a mid-range hotel, then this is your place. It is like a college dorm and has the sound-proofing of one as well. In the morning, we could hear those around us showering and laughing as they left (very early) to start their day.Some of the front desk people are very nice and helpful. However, our first night there my friend got mugged on a nearby street, someone came up behind her in a mask and snatched her purse out from under her arm. When we went back to the hotel to figure out next steps, they quickly said, yes that is a bad street. Things that would have been helpful BEFORE we walked around the area with our map. I'm amazed they don't give some specific warning rather than the general watch out for pickpocketsBarcelona was a beautiful city, but this obviously put a huge damper on it for us. The police there are a joke and do not care for Americans at all. I would stay somewhere else, unless you are on a tight budget and have big, heavy-set, intimidating people with you. If you are just traveling for fun, do yourself a favor for your safety and stay elsewhere please. 
