<Author>Travel-Owl-2
<Content>Agreat base for this wonderful city We have just returned from a great four day break in Barcelona 鈥?our first visit to the city. We booked everything rather last minute so my first three choices for hotels couldn鈥檛 take us. So, based on reviews on Trip Advisor and in a recent travel supplement review, we booked into the Hotel Jardi. In short, we got exactly what we had been led to expect from this hotel. The best thing about the hotel is its location and eternally pleasant staff. The hotel is on the lovely Plaza Sant Josef Oriol and although I would not agree with other reviewers who claim the location is quiet, it is not on a main road and it is probably a lot quieter than many other parts of the city. The plaza was charming with plenty options for breakfast within a stone鈥檚 throw of base. The hotel offers good value (we paid just less than 拢300 for four nights in an external larger double room with a balcony). Now, don鈥檛 expect to have space to practice your salsa in these 鈥榣arge鈥?rooms and the balcony is crowded with two people standing on it, but the location is great, the views are lovely and there is a nice 鈥榝eel鈥?about the place. In short we would stay there again, especially since you don鈥檛 actually spend a lot of time in your hotel on these weekend breaks.I would probably suggest that you don鈥檛 have breakfast at the hotel 鈥?why would you with so many wonderful options within a five minute walk. Yes, the little square is lovely but why not walk five minutes to the Boqueria Market just across the Ramblas from the hotel and dine like a king with the locals? We had the most amazing wild mushrooms, served up with asparagus and a little fresh pesto, on homemade bread. Or head out the back, right-hand door of the market and have the best Spanish breakfast in town on the sunny terrace of 鈥楻a鈥? 
