<Author>Tess
<Content>Perfect Location! My husband and I spent our New Year's week in Barcelona and stayed in Hotel Jardi. Like the prior reviews here, it was kind of tough getting there because the cab driver dropped us off at La Rambla and although it was relatively close to the hotel, it was a pain because we had several luggages. Then, here comes the stairs ...and it was not fun, especially if you're lugging off several pieces of luggages!!! Nobody was there to help you either!PROS - The major asset of this hotel is its location. We had a room with balcony facing the courtyard and it was worth paying the extra 6 euros per night to get this room. We watched the hustle and bustle of activities going on at Plaza del Pi from our balcony. It's close proximity to La Rambla and to the Liceu Metro Station is a BIG PLUS. We walk up and down La Rambla, from the Colon statue to Plaza Catalunya. La Boqueria Market is about 5 minutes from the hotel as well. There is also a huge supermarket along La Rambla that have very reasonable prices. The staff were very friendly and helpful. They offer breakfast on site though we never ate there as there are several other places to eat nearby. The cleaning staff cleaned our room on a daily basis.CONS - Our room was VERY spartan. We have the standard double room, and having just stayed in a timeshare facility in Italy prior to coming here....we wanted to turn around and move to a different hotel. The bathroom was very small, especially the shower. My husband feels claustrophobic everytime he takes a shower. For the price that we paid for this hotel, especially since its during the holidays...I could say that it's worth it. I might come back again if I don't see anything that's as good of a location that'll cost the same. However, I will probably search around first. 
