<Content>Perfect for per-cruise We are travelers who like to go off the beaten path to get the feel the place we are visiting. We are very active aged 58 and 60, and this was for a stay before a 12 day cruise so we had LUGGAGE--a large rolling case (48.5lbs), a rolling garment bag(35lbs), a small rolling case (32lbs) and a backpack.With all this we took the airport bus and easily rolled our luggage to the hotel, if you take the time to study maps before you leave home the square and hotel are easy to find. Yes, there is a steep flight of stairs to carry your stuff up, but if we can do it--so can the younger and sturdier crowd.We arrived at the hotel at 9am and were pleasantly greeted, we left our luggage in the back of the breakfast room, took care of check-in and were told that our room would be ready by about 11am. The area is perfect for exploring.We had a small room on the top floor with a terrace. It was perfect!!! The terrace was huge, with comfortable chairs and a full table, overlooking the church and in the top of the trees of the placa.By some inventive rearranging (we moved the bed against the wall and used the luggage as a headboard we were able to completely open the french doors which made the tiny room seem bigger.The room was very clean, the shower in the bathrrom great and the terrace devine. The people at the desk were very friendly and helpful. I saw them advice other tourists about securing their belongings while in town, they did everything possible to be sure that you had a wonderful visit to this wonderful city.As stated in previuos reviews the location is wonderful, just up the walkway from the hotel are little cafes for coffee and CHOCOLATE in the morning. You are close enough to La Rambles to wander over for the excitement, but then you can escape to your own little hideaway in the Barri Gothic.The hotel called a taxi to take us to thge port--it came right to the door of the hotel.If you are looking for an American hotel--this is not it. If you want a European experience at a great price--the Jardi is for you. 
