<Content>Hotel Jardi We just spent 1 night in the hotel Jardi on Nov. 10, 2005. The hotel was very clean but very very small. The location to La Rambla was terrific, a 2 minute walk. Our room was on the 5th floor across from the elevator. This was no problem as it was off season and very quiet. I would imagine that during the In season it would be not the greatest room to have because of the additional noise from the elevator. We had a small double bed. After we got our 3 suitcases in there was hardly any room to move around. We had a bath with a shower. There was no hairdryer. (I bring my own always) However, they would rent you one for 10E. There was a safe in the teeny closet which also had a fee. There were french doors that opened onto a small square that included a church. Not really any cars. However, the noise that came up from this square ALL night long kept us up most of the night. It was just awful. To get to the lobby of the hotel you have to climb up 24 stairs and carrying 2 carryons and 1 large suitcase was quite the hassle after our cab let us off on La Rambla. We had to walk to the hotel which was only like one block. This was no problem. But the stairs were. Then after checking in, you had to walk up 6/7 more stairs to the tiny elevator. (I am thinking that most elevators in Europe are tiny) There was room for 1 person and 2 carryons/or just two people and no luggage. We had breakfast in the morning at the hotel. Toast, croissant, jam, orange juice(not fresh) and a cup of coffee each. It was 5.50E/person. Since we wanted to do a few minutes of shopping this was the best bet and it was pretty decent. The people in the lobby were very very helpful and friendly. They called a cab for us in the morning and it came right to the door! We were surprised since the night before the driver left us off on La Ramble. Again taking the suitcases down those stairs was a hassle. Would I stay there again, Yes but unless I had a bigger room, only for one night. Ours 